properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued February 7 at 2:42PM PST until February 8 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Portland OR
properties.description:
* WHAT....High surf expected.

* WHERE...South Washington Coast.

* WHEN...Until 7 PM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Sneaker waves can surge high up the beach without
warning, catching an inattentive individual off guard. These
waves can move with great speed further up the beach than you
expect. No place on the beach is too high for a wave to reach.
properties.instruction:
A High Surf Advisory means that high surf will affect beaches in
the advisory area, producing rip currents, sneaker waves and
localized beach erosion.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM PST SATURDAY
